cs.DC, cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.SE, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper presents a task-parallel algorithm for sparse incomplete Cholesky factorization that utilizes a 2D sparse partitioned-block layout of a matrix. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also likely as the paper discusses a factorization algorithm and presents a performance evaluation on matrices from the University of Florida sparse matrix collection. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is another possible category as the paper deals with numerical algorithms for Cholesky factorization. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper presents a portable tasking API that incorporates different tasking backends and device-specific features using an open-source framework for manycore platforms. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also a possible category as the paper presents a performance evaluation on different manycore architectures.
